1. MISSION & PURPOSE
   Karakalpak Voice is an independent media platform dedicated to the 
   Karakalpak people, their culture, sovereignty, and historical heritage.
   Our goal is to deliver authentic information in four languages:
   - Karakalpak (Karakalpak tili)
   - Russian (Русский язык)
   - English (English)
   - Polish (Język polski)

2. INTELLECTUAL PROPERTY
   All content published on https://karakalpakvoice.org (including but not 
   limited to text, translations, historical documents, emblem graphics, 
   and code structure) is the intellectual property of the Karakalpak Voice Team.

3. USAGE POLICY
   [ALLOW] You are encouraged to:
   - Share links to our articles using social networks.
   - Quote short excerpts with a clear reference (hyperlink) to the source.
   - Use materials for educational and non-commercial purposes to promote 
     Karakalpak culture.

   [FORBIDDEN] You may NOT:
   - Copy and republish full articles without written permission.
   - Alter or distort the meaning of our content (Fake News).
   - Use our branding (Logo, Emblem) to mislead the public.

4. DISCLAIMER
   We stand for Truth and Justice. The platform operates in accordance with 
   international norms of freedom of speech and press.

